<plot>Paul Wooley lives in a pastel-coloured world of seashells and whale songs with his cake-baking wife and their 9 year old daughter, Mary, who delights them with the fruits of her violin lessons. On her birthday Mary gets her own violin and the family get a new neighbour, a middle-aged rocker with a head full of the virtues of valve amps and German mikes. When the Woolys see Bill's flying V and he sees Amy's instrument presumptions are drawn, strings are tightened and a major dischord begins.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?427033</url></doc>
